Cocaine worth R2.8m has been discovered hidden in a container that recently arrived at Table Bay Harbour. (SAPS) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories The Boys and Girls Club of Protea Glen, Soweto, is keeping school kids off the streets by diverting their attention to education and wellness through an after-school programme.WATCH Cape Town - Cocaine weighing about 7kg was found in a container at a depot in Maitland on Thursday, Western Cape police said. Cleaning staff found seven blocks of the drug in the side panel of an empty container at a depot in Maitland, Lieutenant-Colonel Andrè Traut said. The drug had an estimated street value of R2.8m. The container arrived at Table Bay harbour recently. Police would determine where it came from and if SA was its final destination.     24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  